                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>In every case, the miniatures are on parchment folios that are of a slightly different size than the surrounding folios</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>Recto of the fore guard leaf (<locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">fols. iv(erso), </locus>), and <locus target="#141v #142r #142v" facs="143 144">141v, 142r, 142v</locus> blank, save for some scrawls</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>Some folios have severe water stains</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                          the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout) or below the line
                          ((<locus target="#45v #47r #48v #53r #62v #119r #122v" facs="047 048 050 054 064 120 124">folss. 45v, 47r, 48v, 53r, 62v, 119r, 122v, </locus>, etc.). This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to
                          avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., (<locus target="#21r #23v #32r #32v" facs="022 025 033 034">21r, 23v, 32r, 32v</locus>, etc.)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#55r" facs="056">Fol. 55r</locus> A note in red ink and circled in red marks the midpoint of the Psalms</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>
                          Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#14v #17r #123v" facs="106 018 125">folss. 14v, 17r, 123v, </locus>);
                          and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#73r #115v" facs="074 117">73r, 115v</locus>)</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards covered with tooled leather, headband and tailband.</decoNote>
